---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="The UN-TILTED Educator Dashboard"
  description="Classroom resources for Grades 6–12. Evidence-based emotional regulation tools delivered through cinematic storytelling and gameplay."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="edu-hero">
    <div class="hero-bg"></div>
    <div class="container hero-content">
      <div class="hero-eyebrow-row">
        <span class="eyebrow">For Educators</span>
        <span class="grade-badge">Grades 6–12</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        The <em>"UN-TILTED"</em><br />
        Educator Dashboard
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Classroom Resources for Grades 6–12
      </p>
      <p class="hero-body">
        Evidence-based emotional regulation tools delivered through<br />
        cinematic storytelling and gameplay.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-skills">
        {['Pause', 'Breathe', 'Cool Down', 'Connect'].map(skill => (
          <span class="skill-chip">{skill}</span>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Body: Sidebar + Content -->
  <div class="edu-body">
    <div class="container edu-layout">

      <!-- Sticky Left Nav -->
      <aside class="edu-nav">
        <p class="nav-heading">Resources</p>
        <nav class="nav-links">
          <a href="#start-here" class="nav-link">
            <span class="nav-num">01</span>
            <span>The Foundation</span>
          </a>
          <a href="#activity-pack" class="nav-link">
            <span class="nav-num">02</span>
            <span>Activity Pack</span>
          </a>
          <a href="#visual-deck" class="nav-link">
            <span class="nav-num">03</span>
            <span>Visual Deck</span>
          </a>
          <a href="#assessment" class="nav-link">
            <span class="nav-num">04</span>
            <span>Assessment</span>
          </a>
        </nav>

        <div class="nav-divider"></div>

        <div class="nav-standards">
          <p class="nav-standards-label">Aligned with</p>
          <div class="nav-chips">
            <span class="std-chip">CASEL</span>
            <span class="std-chip">Common Core ELA</span>
            <span class="std-chip">State SEL Standards</span>
            <span class="std-chip">Grades 6–12</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="nav-divider"></div>

        <a href="/connect" class="btn btn-outline">Get in Touch</a>
      </aside>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="edu-content">

        <!-- Section 01: Start Here -->
        <section class="content-section" id="start-here">
          <div class="section-header">
            <span class="eyebrow">The Foundation</span>
            <h2 class="subheadline">The "Start Here" Guide</h2>
            <p class="resource-subtitle">The Master PDF</p>
          </div>
          <p class="body-lg">
            This is the single document that holds the whole vision together.
            The complete framework — narrative, science, and step-by-step
            classroom implementation — in one place.
          </p>

          <div class="included-items">
            <p class="included-label">What's inside:</p>

            <div class="included-item">
              <div class="included-icon">
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5z"/><path d="M2 17l10 5 10-5"/><path d="M2 12l10 5 10-5"/></svg>
              </div>
              <div class="included-body">
                <strong>The Hero's Journey Narrative</strong>
                <span>The explanation of the move from Recognition to Mastery — the arc that connects the film, the game, and the classroom.</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="included-item">
              <div class="included-icon">
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><path d="M3 9h18M9 21V9"/></svg>
              </div>
              <div class="included-body">
                <strong>SEL Skill Mapping</strong>
                <span>A one-page chart showing exactly how Pause, Breathe, Cool Down, and Connect align with state standards and CASEL competencies.</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="included-item">
              <div class="included-icon">
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/><polyline points="10 9 9 9 8 9"/></svg>
              </div>
              <div class="included-body">
                <strong>The "Say / Do" Script</strong>
                <span>Step-by-step instructions for running the full Art Project → Film → Game sequence in your classroom.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="resource-cta">
            <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg placeholder-link" aria-disabled="true">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/><polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/><line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3"/></svg>
              Download Master PDF
            </a>
            <span class="coming-soon-note">Available at launch</span>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 02: Activity Pack -->
        <section class="content-section" id="activity-pack">
          <div class="section-header">
            <span class="eyebrow">Printable Assets</span>
            <h2 class="subheadline">The Activity Pack</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="body-lg">
            Download just the handouts you need for the day. Each asset is
            designed to stand alone — use them together or in any sequence
            that works for your classroom.
          </p>

          <div class="assets-grid">

            <div class="asset-card card">
              <div class="asset-icon-area yellow">
                <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="5"/><path d="M3 21c0-4.4 4-8 9-8s9 3.6 9 8"/></svg>
              </div>
              <div class="asset-body">
                <span class="asset-label">Expression Gallery</span>
                <h3 class="asset-title">The "Sticky Stan" Expression Gallery</h3>
                <p class="asset-desc">
                  A high-res PDF of the full emotional expression faces students
                  will reference for their art project. Stan's expressions map
                  directly to the four core skill states.
                </p>
                <div class="asset-specs">
                  <span class="tag">High-Res PDF</span>
                  <span class="tag">Art Project</span>
                  <span class="tag">Grades 6–12</span>
                </div>
                <button class="btn btn-outline placeholder-btn" disabled>
                  <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/><polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/><line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3"/></svg>
                  Coming Soon
                </button>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="asset-card card">
              <div class="asset-icon-area purple">
                <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><path d="M9 3v18M15 9H9M15 15H9"/></svg>
              </div>
              <div class="asset-body">
                <span class="asset-label">Body Mapping</span>
                <h3 class="asset-title">The "Analog MOD" Worksheet</h3>
                <p class="asset-desc">
                  The humanoid body-mapping template for mapping "internal code"
                  and word-fills. Students locate where emotions live in their
                  body and name what activates them.
                </p>
                <div class="asset-specs">
                  <span class="tag">Printable PDF</span>
                  <span class="tag">SEL Activity</span>
                  <span class="tag">Individual & Group</span>
                </div>
                <button class="btn btn-outline placeholder-btn" disabled>
                  <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/><polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/><line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3"/></svg>
                  Coming Soon
                </button>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="asset-card card">
              <div class="asset-icon-area green">
                <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M4 19.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 17H20"/><path d="M6.5 2H20v20H6.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2z"/></svg>
              </div>
              <div class="asset-body">
                <span class="asset-label">Universe Lore</span>
                <h3 class="asset-title">The "Intel Notebook" Pages</h3>
                <p class="asset-desc">
                  Printable versions of Aaron's lore — Mind Ninjas, Tilt Shogun,
                  and the full UN-TILTED universe — so students can read the
                  "intel" even without a screen.
                </p>
                <div class="asset-specs">
                  <span class="tag">Printable PDF</span>
                  <span class="tag">Lore & Narrative</span>
                  <span class="tag">Screenless Option</span>
                </div>
                <button class="btn btn-outline placeholder-btn" disabled>
                  <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/><polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/><line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3"/></svg>
                  Coming Soon
                </button>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 03: Visual Deck -->
        <section class="content-section" id="visual-deck">
          <div class="section-header">
            <span class="eyebrow">The Presentation</span>
            <h2 class="subheadline">The Visual Deck</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="body-lg">
            The ready-to-project slide deck for your classroom. Everything
            you need built in — Pixar examples, the film link, the game
            mission, and hashtag instructions.
          </p>
          <p class="body-lg">
            Open it. Project it. Teach it. Available in both Google Slides
            and PowerPoint so you can edit to fit your class.
          </p>

          <div class="deck-features">
            {[
              'Pixar / film examples built-in',
              'Film screening link embedded',
              'Game mission walkthrough slides',
              'Hashtag + social challenge instructions',
              'Fully editable — customize for your class',
              'Speaker notes on every slide',
            ].map(f => (
              <div class="deck-feature">
                <span class="check-icon">
                  <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
                </span>
                <span>{f}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>

          <div class="deck-cta-row">
            <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary placeholder-link" aria-disabled="true">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6"/><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"/><line x1="10" y1="14" x2="21" y2="3"/></svg>
              Open in Google Slides
            </a>
            <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline placeholder-link" aria-disabled="true">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/><polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/><line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3"/></svg>
              Download as PowerPoint
            </a>
            <span class="coming-soon-note">Available at launch</span>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 04: Assessment -->
        <section class="content-section" id="assessment">
          <div class="section-header">
            <span class="eyebrow">Assessment &amp; Reflection</span>
            <h2 class="subheadline">Assessment &amp;<br />Reflection Tools</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="body-lg">
            Fast, focused tools that close the loop — connecting what students
            experience in the game to what they'll apply in their lives.
          </p>

          <div class="assessment-grid">

            <div class="assessment-card card">
              <div class="assessment-card-header">
                <div class="assessment-icon">
                  <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M9 11l3 3L22 4"/><path d="M21 12v7a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h11"/></svg>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <span class="assessment-meta">3-Minute Reflection</span>
                  <h3 class="assessment-title">The Exit Ticket</h3>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="assessment-desc">
                A quick end-of-session reflection sheet where students identify
                which "Enemy" they faced in the game and which SEL skill they'll
                commit to using at home.
              </p>
              <div class="assessment-prompts">
                <p class="prompts-label">Reflection prompts include:</p>
                <ul class="prompts-list">
                  <li>Which emotional "Enemy" did you face today?</li>
                  <li>Which skill did you use to beat it?</li>
                  <li>Where will you use this skill this week?</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="assessment-placeholder">
                <button class="btn btn-outline placeholder-btn" disabled>Coming Soon</button>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="assessment-card card">
              <div class="assessment-card-header">
                <div class="assessment-icon">
                  <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M21 15a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h14a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"/></svg>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <span class="assessment-meta">Systems Thinking Prompts</span>
                  <h3 class="assessment-title">The Discussion Guide</h3>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="assessment-desc">
                Specific discussion prompts differentiated by tier — designed to
                surface the systems thinking concepts underneath the game
                narrative.
              </p>

              <div class="tier-tabs">
                <div class="tier-tab active-tier">
                  <span class="tier-label">Middle School</span>
                  <div class="tier-placeholder">
                    <p class="tier-desc">Discussion prompts focused on personal emotion recognition and peer connection. <span class="tier-grade">Grades 6–8</span></p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="tier-tab">
                  <span class="tier-label">High School</span>
                  <div class="tier-placeholder">
                    <p class="tier-desc">Systems-level prompts exploring emotional regulation, identity, and community impact. <span class="tier-grade">Grades 9–12</span></p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="assessment-placeholder">
                <button class="btn btn-outline placeholder-btn" disabled>Coming Soon</button>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </section>

      </div><!-- /edu-content -->
    </div><!-- /edu-layout -->
  </div><!-- /edu-body -->

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section-sm edu-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-inner">
        <div class="cta-text">
          <h2 class="subheadline">Bring it to your school.</h2>
          <p class="body-lg">
            Ready to run the full Art Project → Film → Game sequence?
            Reach out to bring a live activation to your campus.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="cta-actions">
          <a href="/activations" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">School Activations</a>
          <a href="/connect" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">Get in Touch</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  /* ─── Hero ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .edu-hero {
    min-height: 80vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    padding-block: 8rem 5rem;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .hero-bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 20% 60%, rgba(245, 200, 66, 0.07) 0%, transparent 55%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 80% 20%, rgba(124, 92, 191, 0.1) 0%, transparent 50%),
      linear-gradient(135deg, #080316 0%, #12062a 60%, #1c0832 100%);
  }

  .hero-content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .hero-eyebrow-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .grade-badge {
    padding: 0.25em 0.875em;
    background: rgba(245, 200, 66, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(245, 200, 66, 0.3);
    border-radius: 100px;
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 900;
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 7rem);
    line-height: 0.95;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    color: #f5f0ff;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .hero-title em {
    font-style: normal;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .hero-sub {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: rgba(210, 200, 240, 0.8);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  .hero-body {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.5vw, 1.15rem);
    color: var(--fg-2);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .hero-skills {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.625rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .skill-chip {
    padding: 0.35em 1em;
    border: 1px solid rgba(245, 200, 66, 0.25);
    border-radius: 100px;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: rgba(245, 200, 66, 0.06);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  /* ─── Body Layout ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .edu-body {
    background: linear-gradient(to right, #080316 0%, #1c0832 100%);
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    padding-block: 5rem;
  }

  .edu-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 210px 1fr;
    gap: 0;
    align-items: start;
  }

  /* ─── Left Nav ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .edu-nav {
    position: sticky;
    top: 7rem;
    padding-right: 2.5rem;
    border-right: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .nav-heading {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--fg-3);
  }

  .nav-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.125rem;
  }

  .nav-link {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--fg-2);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.15s, background 0.15s;
  }

  .nav-link:hover {
    color: var(--fg);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
  }

  .nav-num {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: rgba(245, 200, 66, 0.4);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 1.5rem;
  }

  .nav-divider {
    height: 1px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    margin-block: 0.25rem;
  }

  .nav-standards-label {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--fg-3);
    margin-bottom: 0.625rem;
  }

  .nav-chips {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.375rem;
  }

  .std-chip {
    padding: 0.3em 0.75em;
    border: 1px solid rgba(245, 200, 66, 0.2);
    border-radius: 100px;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: rgba(245, 200, 66, 0.7);
    background: rgba(245, 200, 66, 0.05);
    display: inline-block;
    width: fit-content;
  }

  /* ─── Right Content ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .edu-content {
    padding-left: 3.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .content-section {
    padding-block: 3.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .content-section:first-child { padding-top: 0; }
  .content-section:last-child  { border-bottom: none; }

  .section-header {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .section-header .eyebrow { margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }

  .resource-subtitle {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--fg-3);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-top: -0.25rem;
  }

  /* ─── Included Items ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .included-items {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    padding: 1.75rem;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
  }

  .included-label {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--fg-3);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .included-item {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .included-icon {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background: rgba(245, 200, 66, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(245, 200, 66, 0.15);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-top: 0.1rem;
  }

  .included-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
  }

  .included-body strong {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--fg);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .included-body span {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--fg-2);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .resource-cta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .coming-soon-note {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--fg-3);
